SIMPLE: response
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Response
<hw>Re*sponse"</hw> <pr>(r?*sp?ns")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>response</ets>, <ets>respons</ets>, F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧ponse</ets>,
from L. <ets>responsum</ets>, from <ets>respondere</ets>. See
<er>Respond</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
responding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An answer or reply.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Reply to an objection in formal disputation.</def> <au>I.
Watts.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The answer of the
people or congregation to the priest or clergyman, in the litany and
other parts of divine service.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <fld>(R.C.Ch.)</fld>
<def>A kind of anthem sung after the lessons of matins and some other
parts of the office.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
repetition of the given subject in a fugue by another part on the fifth
above or fourth below.</def> <au>Busby.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Responseless</ent>⟦br⟧
